
[1]haft

   H`AFT, n. [L. capio.] A handle; that part of an instrument or vessel
   which is taken into the hand, and by which it is held and used. It is
   used chiefly for the part of a sword or dagger by which it is held; the
   hilt.

   H`AFT, v.t. To set in a haft; to furnish with a handle.
